---
import ProjectDetail from '../../layouts/ProjectDetail.astro';

const demoImage = '/screenshots/physics-rag.png';
---

<ProjectDetail
  title="Physics RAG"
  description="A research assistant over physics papers and textbooks. Upload PDFs or link arXiv articles, then get grounded, citation-aware answers while you learn."
  tags={['RAG', 'ChromaDB', 'FastAPI', 'React']}
  github="https://github.com/MariamKhubashvilii/Physics-Chatbot"
  accent="blue"
  demoImage={demoImage}
>
  <section class="project-grid">
    <article class="project-card summary-card">
      <h2>Project summary</h2>
      <p>
        Physics RAG lets physics students research across multiple authoritative sources at once. Upload PDFs or paste an arXiv link, ask a question, and the system synthesizes an answer from textbooks like Griffiths, Feynman, and Carroll — plus your own notes — with exact sources and page numbers.
      </p>
      <div class="summary-list">
        <div>
          <strong>Grounded answers</strong>
          <p>Every response is backed by retrieved passages and includes precise citations and page references, so you can verify what you learn.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Flexible input</strong>
          <p>Combine textbooks, uploaded PDFs, and direct arXiv URLs into a single searchable knowledge base.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="project-card detail-card">
      <h2>What this project shows</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Document ingestion from PDFs and arXiv links.</li>
        <li>Vector embeddings with semantic search and reranking.</li>
        <li>Citation-aware answer generation grounded in sources.</li>
        <li>Full-stack build: FastAPI backend, React frontend.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section">
    <div class="section-content">
      <h2>How it works</h2>
      <p>
        Documents are loaded through PDF and arXiv fetching modules, chunked into manageable segments, and embedded using sentence-transformers. When you ask a question, ChromaDB retrieves the relevant passages, a reranker prioritizes the most pertinent ones, and Groq's LLM generates an answer grounded in those retrieved sources.
      </p>

      <div class="section-grid">
        <div>
          <h3>Pipeline</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Load PDFs and fetch arXiv papers</li>
            <li>Chunk and embed with sentence-transformers</li>
            <li>Retrieve from ChromaDB, then rerank</li>
            <li>Generate cited answers via Groq</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Tech stack</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Backend: FastAPI (Python)</li>
            <li>Frontend: React + Vite</li>
            <li>Vector store: ChromaDB</li>
            <li>Embeddings: sentence-transformers; LLM: Groq</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="project-section project-usage">
    <h2>Run it</h2>
    <p>
      For the backend, create a virtual environment, install dependencies from <code>requirements.txt</code>, add your Groq API key to <code>.env</code>, then run <code>uvicorn backend.main:app --reload</code>. For the frontend, move into the frontend directory, install npm dependencies, and run <code>npm run dev</code>.
    </p>
    <div class="usage-card">
      <div>
        <strong>Setup</strong>
        <p>Python environment, Groq API key, and Node for the React frontend.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <strong>Best for</strong>
        <p>Physics students who want grounded, citable answers while studying.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectDetail>
